      <hedline>
        <hl1>Colombia Needs Help</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ben Heller letter says Colombia deserves US aid because American drug war has exported destabilization and destruction to that country (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>While Anthony Lewis rightly points out the futility of fighting a ''drug war'' by trying to choke off foreign supply of narcotics (column, June 24), Colombia nonetheless deserves American aid.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>While Anthony Lewis rightly points out the futility of fighting a ''drug war'' by trying to choke off foreign supply of narcotics (column, June 24), Colombia nonetheless deserves American aid.</p>
        <p>America's drug war has exported destabilization and destruction to Colombia, which at great cost fought off a hijacking of the state by professional narco-criminals in the late 1980's and the 90's, only now to face two entrenched rebel groups fearsomely armed by drug money. Without American aid, Colombia will struggle to restore public order.</p>
        <p>Those two rebel groups menace Latin America's longest-running democracy and will continue to do so regardless of any United States drug policy changes. Colombia deserves aid not as an instrument of our drug war, but as recompense for the harm our drug war has wrought on its society.</p>
        <p>BEN HELLER  New York, June 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
